Section 72. With regard to land, natural resources, and environment, the State should act as follows:
(1) Lay down rules on the use of land throughout the country in accordance with the conditions of each area, including the actual state of the land and the law on town planning, and secure compliance with such rules efficiently, whereby rules on the use of land shall also enable local communities to participate in the determination thereof;
(2) Prescribe measures for the fair distribution of landholding rights, and enable farmers to have ownership or rights in land for agriculture by land reform or other means, including providing assistance to facilitate land acquisition and water sources for farming;
(3) Provide town planning for every province and enforce it efficiently so as to achieve urban and rural development in conformity with the needs of the area;
(4) Provide a scheme for the efficient and sustainable management and preservation of natural resources, whereby local communities must be allowed to participate in and benefit from such management and preservation;
(5) Promote, maintain, and protect the quality of the environment in accordance with the sustainable development principle, and control and eliminate pollution that affects health, welfare, and quality of life of the public.
